@NODE "AmiIntro" "Introduction"
@font xen.font 8

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

  People complain that Amiga companies do not know what the Amiga users want,
 well, this file is there to solve just this problem as well as to give
 software/hardware developers future ideas.  Now there is no real
 excuse for any Amiga company to NOT comply with the users' demands.  Some
 people say it's a bit selfish doing this, but what people must realize is
 that the Amiga users left are not stupid, they are professionals when it
 comes to the Amiga and who else knows better what the new Amigas should do 
 but the Amiga public who has been using them for up to 10 - 11 years!
 This guide is basically a giant wish list for the new Amigas, however it
 also shows what ideas Amiga users have an possibly some new areas for Amiga
 software/hardware to develop in.

  This guide is not a press release, or anything official, it is what users
 want to happen, not what WILL happen.  This was produced separate to Amiga
 International and any other Amiga company.

  This guide assumes that 24bit Graphics and 16bit Sound are standard and
 should not have to be repeated.

 All Hardware and Software is Copyright their makers...

 @{b}So, do you have any comments or anything you want added?
 @{"Mail me" Link "AmiAuthor"} and I'll be happy to put it in.@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "AmiAuthor" "Authors And Who Helped Make This File"
@font xen.font 8

 @{b}@{u}Authors@{uu}@{ub}

  This guide is compiled with the help of the Undernet @{b}#Amiga@{ub} and
 @{b}#AmigaCafe@{ub} channels.  I realize that not all of this is accepted by all
 users, that would be impossible to accomplish, but any difference in
 opinion is mentioned and detailed.

  This guide was compiled by Me, Wayne Martin (TB).  I have been using
 Amigas right from the start back in the mid 80's and have loved them ever
